FBIS4-24056 "drafr120_d_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Lesotho British Adviser To Help Set Up Defense Ministry British Adviser To Help Set Up Defense Ministry MB2106161794 Maseru Radio Lesotho in English 1130 GMT 21 Jun 94 MB2106161794 Maseru Radio Lesotho English BFN [Text] A civilian adviser from the British Ministry of Defense, Mr. Phil Jones, has assumed his duties in Maseru in secondment to the Lesotho Government to assist with the establishment of a Ministry of Defense. According to a press statement released by the British High Commission in Maseru, Mr. Jones' duties will include guidance on procurement, the production of annual plans, advice on financial central systems, the establishment of appropriate office procedures and the provision of hands-on training support. Mr. Jones is expected to return to the United Kingdom at the end of March 1995 on completion of his assignment.
